library(tigris)
## To enable caching of data, set `options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE)`
## in your R script or .Rprofile.
setwd('C:/GES_486/Rworks/Lab4/Projects/')
us_value <- get_acs(
  geography = "state",
  variables = "B19013_001",
  year = 2019,
  survey = "acs1",
  geometry = TRUE,
  resolution = "20m"
)
## Getting data from the 2019 1-year ACS
## The 1-year ACS provides data for geographies with populations of 65,000 and greater.
## Downloading feature geometry from the Census website.  To cache shapefiles for use in future sessions, set `options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE)`.
library(ggiraph)
library(scales)
us_value_shifted <- us_value %>%
  shift_geometry(position = "outside") %>%
  mutate(tooltip = paste(NAME, estimate, sep = ", state Household Income: $"))

pl <- ggplot(us_value_shifted, aes(fill = estimate)) + 
  geom_sf_interactive(aes(tooltip = tooltip, data_id = NAME), 
                      size = 0.1) + 
  scale_fill_viridis_c(option = "plasma", labels = label_dollar()) + 
  labs(title = "Household income value by state in US, 2019",
       caption = "Data source: 2019 1-year ACS, US Census Bureau",
       fill = "ACS Estimate") + 
  theme_void() 

pl <- pl +
   ggspatial::annotation_scale(
    location = "bl",
    bar_cols = c("grey60", "white"),
    text_family = "ArcherPro Book"
  ) +

  ggspatial::annotation_north_arrow(
    location = "tr", which_north = "grid",
    style = ggspatial::north_arrow_orienteering
  )
  
girafe(ggobj = pl) %>%
  girafe_options(opts_hover(css = "fill:cyan;"), 
                 opts_zoom(max = 10))
## Scale on map varies by more than 10%, scale bar may be inaccurate
ggsave("Household_Income_plot.png", pl, height = 5, width = 7, dpi = "screen")
